SIMPLE: withal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Withal
<hw>With*al"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[<ets>With</ets> +
<ets>all</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>With this; with that.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He will scarce be pleased <qex>withal</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Together with this; likewise; at the same time; in
addition; also.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fy on possession⟦br⟧
But if a man be virtuous <qex>withal</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If you choose that, then I am yours <qex>withal</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How modest in exception, and <qex>withal</qex>⟦br⟧
How terrible in constant resolution.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Withal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Withal
<hw>With*al"</hw>, <pos>prep.</pos> <def>With; -- put after its object,
at the end of sentence or clause in which it stands.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This diamond he greets your wife <qex>withal</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whatsoever uncleanness it be that a man shall be defiled
<qex>withal</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Lev. v. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Withamite</ent>⟦br⟧
